# sapstack Rules for Cursor

This rule applies whenever Cursor is editing files in this repository. It enforces SAP advisory best practices across all conversations.

## Universal Rules

1. **NEVER hardcode** company codes, G/L accounts, cost centers, or org units. Ask the user or read from `.sapstack/config.yaml`.
2. **ALWAYS ask for environment** before answering: SAP release, deployment model, industry, company code.
3. **ALWAYS distinguish ECC vs S/4HANA** behavior explicitly (BSEG vs ACDOCA, FD32 vs UKM_BP, F.05 vs FAGL_FC_VAL).
4. **Transport request required** for any config change.
5. **Simulate before actual run** — AFAB, F.13, FAGL_FC_VAL, KSU5, MR11, F110 must use Test Run first.
6. **Never recommend SE16N** data edits in production.
7. **Always provide T-code + SPRO menu path**.

## Response Format

```
## 🔍 Issue
## 🧠 Root Cause
## ✅ Check (T-code + Table/Field)
## 🛠 Fix (numbered steps)
## 🛡 Prevention
## 📖 SAP Note (only if verified in data/sap-notes.yaml)
```

## Knowledge Sources

- `plugins/sap-<module>/skills/sap-<module>/SKILL.md` — module knowledge (English source of truth)
- `plugins/sap-<module>/skills/sap-<module>/references/ko/` — Korean guides
- `data/tcodes.yaml` — authoritative T-code registry (never mention unlisted T-codes)
- `data/sap-notes.yaml` — verified SAP Note catalog (never cite unverified numbers)
- `agents/*.md` — specialized prompts (reusable)

## 13 Modules

sap-fi, sap-co, sap-tr (Financials) | sap-mm, sap-sd, sap-pp (Logistics) | sap-hcm, sap-sfsf (HR) | sap-abap, sap-s4-migration, sap-btp, sap-basis, **sap-bc** (Technology + Korean specialization)

**BC = Basis in Korean SAP industry.** Use `sap-bc` for Korean-context Basis topics (한글 Unicode, 망분리, 전자세금계산서, K-SOX). Use `sap-basis` for global English Basis topics. Both are the same functional area; only the localization layer differs.

## ABAP Code Generation

- No `SELECT *` — targeted fields only
- No SELECT inside LOOP — use FOR ALL ENTRIES or JOIN
- Clean Core: no modifications to standard SAP objects, use BAdI/Enhancement/CDS
- S/4HANA: no BSEG, MKPF/MSEG, CALL TRANSACTION in background jobs
- Every BAPI call checks RETURN table for E/A messages
- AUTHORITY-CHECK on sensitive data access
- Korean personal data (주민번호, 연락처) must be masked in logs

